post_text:
This is Teacher Appreciation Week! We are not able to celebrate our teachers this week like we normally would, but that does not mean we do not appreciate all that they do!

During this week, we ask that you send a message, a letter, a picture or a short video to YOUR teacher and thank them for all they do! These little acts of kindness will not go unnoticed and it will allow us to brighten their day and let them know we are so grateful for their time and commitment to our students! ❤️

Staunton IL PTO
April 2 at 10:00 AM ·

Your Student’s Artwork is Ready to View and Order!

In March your student created a unique piece of art that the PTO shipped to Square1Art to be made into stickers as well as other products that you may want to purchase. The stickers are free, and we will get those to your student when the situation allows. Due to the current stay at home order we will not be able to distribute or accept paper orders. However, you can order this artwork online by going to www.square1art.com. Once there, click on shop and search for artwork. You will need to put our state, school name, and student’s name into the search criteria. Orders must be placed online by April 17th. These orders will ship to school in May, and we will distribute them as soon as the situation allows. Proceeds from these sales are used to fund Fine Arts Day each year. We appreciate your support!

Square 1 Art | It Starts With the Art!

post_text:
Hello Staunton Community!

We wanted to share a good resource that one of us recently came across. Please read the information below. From our understanding, it is a limited amount of books, but still a good option for the kids.

Copied for reference:
Amazon today canceled the subscription of books and audio stories for children and students of all ages as long as schools are closed, kids everywhere can instantly stream an incredible collection of stories, including titles across six different languages, that will help them continue dreaming, learning, and just being kids.

All stories are free to stream on your desktop, laptop, phone or tablet using the following link https://stories.audible.com/start-listen

Staunton families,
We hope everyone is geared back up and ready to start school tomorrow after this nice break we have had.

Prior to break, your child should have brought home information regarding their class basket theme for the School of Rock Fundraiser. These baskets will be raffled off at the event.

This event helped the PTO so much last year and we are hopeful it will be just as successful this year! Please help by bringing in an item or items that relate to your basket theme.

The event details are below and I have also included the flier that lists out the basket themes in the comments below.

Thank you so much for supporting the Staunton PTO and the great musicians that will make this event happen!

Staunton PTO

Art Fundraiser:
Fine Arts Day is one of the many activities funded by the PTO. Earlier this week, you child (Pre-K through 4th) brought home a customized order form of their own piece of art. Please consider ordering something with your child’s masterpiece on it so our PTO can continue funding great experiences like Fine Arts Day! We could not do what we do without YOUR support. The order forms must be turned in by April 30th. Ordering online (info is on the form) is encouraged and also allows you to pick a few other pieces that are not on the paper order form. Online orders must also be submitted by April 30th. Artwork orders will be delivered before the end of the school year. As always, thanks for your continued support!

post_text:
Hey Staunton families! We are excited to be starting another school year in our great community. We've already been involved with a couple of projects and school has not even started! With the thanks to all those who support the PTO, we were able to provide the mulch to refresh the playground and we have also secured viewing glasses for the solar eclipse for each student.

text:

post_text:
Just an update - finalized the bookfair today - we did just over $10,000 in sales! 65% of that will be available to the teachers to spend in their classrooms in addition to the $8500 already available from previous Bookfair's. which means that pre-k through 8th will have approximately $15,000 to split between them! Holy cow Staunton - great job!!!! This money is not in cash but can be spent at the scholastic online catalog only - which gives them lots of book options, classroom tools, furniture and extras.
Look for information on our BOGO fair coming in May - this will be 2 evenings only and is an excellent way to get great books for summer readings!
